  "prompt": "Is it true that NASA rejected the Big Bang theory and accepted the vedic explanation ?",
  "response": "No, that statement is not true. NASA has not rejected the Big Bang theory in favor of any Vedic explanation. The Big Bang theory is the leading scientific explanation for the origin and evolution of the universe, supported by extensive observational evidence, including the cosmic microwave background radiation and the observed redshift of galaxies.\n\nWhile various cultural and philosophical traditions, including Vedic texts, may offer their own cosmological explanations, they do not have the empirical support that scientific theories like the Big Bang do. Scientific theories are based on testable predictions and evidence, whereas religious or philosophical texts are not subject to the same empirical scrutiny.\n\nNASA and the broader scientific community continue to support and investigate the Big Bang theory and its implications for understanding the universe's history.",
